Miss Brown, 44, told RadarOnline: 'They’re in their late 20s. They’re professional. They’ve gone to college. They’re in relationships. They’re happy. They’re just like us. Quote unquote.'

The aunt said that following their father's 1995 murder trial it was difficult for the children to experience a normal life.

However Miss Brown and the children's grandmother forced themselves to face Simpson, who they believe killed Nicole and Ron Goldman, for the sake of the children.

Miss Brown said: 'They will always love their dad. I choose to respect that.'

