Miss Brown, a life coach and mental-health 
advocate, recently wrote a memoir about the loss of her 
older sister Nicole, entitled Finding Peace Amid The Chaos.

In the emotional book, she revealed the moment she knew that the man she once called 'Uncle O.J.' was responsible for her sister's death.

She also described how her family's lives were forever shattered on the morning of June 13, 1994, when they found out that Nicole, recently divorced from Simpson, had been stabbed to death outside her Los Angeles home along with her friend Ron Goldman.

She said the grief-stricken family watched on TV as her sister's bloodied corpse was loaded into a van to be taken to the morgue. Miss Brown said she held her mother's shaking hands as she wept: 'That's my kid.' 

